Audi claims to have created the fuel of the future - diesel made from water and carbon dioxide . 
  Experts used renewable energy to convert the carbon dioxide and water into a form of crude oil known as 'blue crude', which was then refined into diesel . 
  The car manufacturer described its breakthrough as the 'fuel of thefuture' and claims it could provide a carbon neutral way of powering vehicles . 
  Audi has already begun using the fuel to power the official car of the German government . 
 